# spartan/ui Conventions

This project uses **spartan/ui** (Brain + Helm). Read `.agents/skills/spartan/SKILL.md` for full workflow.

## Architecture

- **Brain** (`@spartan-ng/brain/*`) — npm packages, do not edit.
- **Helm** (`@spartan-ng/helm/*`) — copied to `libs/ui/`, owned and customizable.

## Required patterns

- Import `*Imports` consts (e.g. `HlmCardImports`) into standalone component `imports`.
- Use `provideSpartanHlm()` in `app.config.ts` for overlay components.
- Register icons with `provideIcons({ lucideXxx })` wherever `<ng-icon>` is used.
- Use semantic Tailwind tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border` — never raw colors like `bg-blue-500`.
- Layout spacing: prefer `gap-*` over `space-*`; use `size-*` when width equals height.
- Use component `variant` / `size` inputs before custom classes.
- Dialogs, sheets, and alert dialogs must include a title (use `sr-only` if hidden).

## CLI

```bash
ng g @spartan-ng/cli:info --json          # project context
ng g @spartan-ng/cli:ui --name=<component> # add component
ng g @spartan-ng/cli:healthcheck --autoFix # after upgrades
```

Helm path: `libs/ui` · Import alias: `@spartan-ng/helm`

## Agent skill

Spartan skill lives at `.agents/skills/spartan/` — follow `rules/styling.md`, `rules/composition.md`, `rules/icons.md`, and `rules/forms.md` when building UI.
